<br>
For the exact details, go in game and make sure you have no one targeted and type /shield. There are in game instructions that should tell you the exact details of it.<br>
<br>
This is a good raid and exp group tool. Good warriors use it, lazy or bad warriors dont. Use it on debuffers and slowers that aggro early or by using the following macro, you can have a quick hotkey for when you see the mob summon random squishy casters.<br>
<br>
/assist                      &lt;~~Assists the mob that is attacking your shield target<br>
/shield                      &lt;~~Sheilds that squishy caster<br>
/assist MAplayername  &lt;~~Normal assist MA hotkey to get you back on mob <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Overlord of Darkwind</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=527339" target="top">Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=romaandamorlita>RomaAndAmorlita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 12:58:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.valonguild.com/vbb/avatar.php?userid=951&dateline=1044705128 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield ???</span><hr size=1> Also, you might wanna /pause 1 or 2 seconds in between commands....I find that if I don't have that second for the target to switch it sometimes won't work. I know every second counts, but I have had it error out without the pause. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sage Roma Emeraldheart</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
