 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xternalx>XternalX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 5:47:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield ???</span><hr size=1> Thank you for your responses! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khementari>Khementari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 6:10:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield ???</span><hr size=1> Take up the ability and learn how to use it. It is a tool we have been given as warriors and if you ignore it you are shortchanging yourself and the people you spend your time with in this game. It is a useful tool. No, it is not the most spectacular thing in the game but I can no longer count the number of lives I have saved by using this ability. More importantly, even when I use this ability and lives are still lost it is the fact that I am trying to help to the best of my ability that gains the respect of my guildies as well as others I group with. People remember &quot;using me as a living shield&quot; and often send much thanks for saving their asses in group or in tell. <br>
<br>
Zarg, 61 Warlord, TT <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kdsktan>kdsktan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 6:40:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield ???</span><hr size=1> I would definitely use it. I tend to set up a couple of hotkeys for cleric/healer and slower instead of the all purpose hotkey someone set out above.<br>
<br>
It has in my experience saved quite a few lives, buying that bit extra time for the heal to get in.<br>
<br>
However, in order for it to be effective you have to know when and how to use it. Heres a couple of tips.<br>
<br>
If your the puller, make sure when u pull the mob that you run straight back and stand next to your slower. That way, if they get aggro, you should alread be right next to them and ready to shield if need be. FOr best results you have to be practically on top of the slower and in front of the mob. Shrink helps too.<br>
<br>
Also, make sure the slower is not the run around like a headless chicken type when their getting beat on otherwise its just a waste of time. If they do run around ask them nicely to stay put, or else you wont bother shielding them.<br>
<br>
Remember the recyle is 3 minutes. This means on normal exp grinding u get to use it normally on every other mob. So, dont automatically mash it just cos the slower/cleric is taking a hit. Taunt bash/kick disarm first and see if that does the business. If not, see if you have time for another taunt, but if the HPs are dropping quick then go ahead and shield. <br>
<br>
Much also depends on how aware your cleric/spot healers are. If they are on the ball, then they will be spot healing the slower as soon as they are getting hit. In those situations, save it for a rainy day.<br>
<br>
ALso, use a /g shield message to that they know you are shielding as they may not necessarily see the action action depending on their filters.<br>
<br>
Its a nice feeling when you use it on a caster and u know and they know that you just saved their ass.<br>
