<br>
One tank /sheilds another who is getting hit by 2+ mobs until the secondary assist gets aggro to reduce it to single encounters.<br>
<br>
Much better than switching tanks over and over.<br>
<br>
Ironfang <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 12:11:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield ???</span><hr size=1> One person tanking multiple elemenetal trash being shielded by another warriors means both warriors are likely to be dead soon.  At any rate, Knights peeling off extra mobs with non damage aggro spells until they can be mezzed is infinitely superior than using shield which actually increases mob DPS to your raid.  Shield effectively increases the damage you take by 25% (though spread out between two persons) and certainly Knights tank significantly better than you taking 25% more damage.  <br>
<br>
Shield represents very inefficient tanking and thus inefficient  healing (CH is not effective if you're taking damage at caster level AC).  Apparently people cared a lot about healing efficiency in the game Knights versus Warrior megathread but you want to constantly use a tool that makes you tank worse than a Knight.  Yes it'll look like you saved someone but the real conclusion to make if shield is being used a lot is that the group should've got a Knight instead because a shielding warrior is an inferior tank compare to a Knight.<br>
<br>
Obviously, there are some situations where /shield is good.  In raid situations sometimes you can afford to sacrifice some efficiency for survival.  But at least for XP groups, if given a choice to use AE Taunt or shield, you should always use AE Taunt, not shield (unless it's low HP aggro, then you might as well try /shield). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=strikingone>StrikingOne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 12:13:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield ???</span><hr size=1> Shield has saved my cleric bot lots! Especially handy when DA is interrupted. <br>
