<br>
The tradeoff is more than just 'I shielded this guy and he didn't die so it must be good.'  For example, if you didn't shield the guy and he died, maybe he'll realize that he was overaggroing and stop overaggroing.  Granted, I don't really see this happening very often... people usually just blame the warrior instead...<br>
<br>
Suffice to say that there are very few situations I can think of where shield couldn't be replaced by smart aggro control on the group's part, which eliminates the problem altogether and is better in the longer run for everyone.  But then, it's not common to find good aggro control in pickup gruops, so maybe that's your only choice. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=strikingone>StrikingOne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/03 3:00:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /SHIELD WORKS</span><hr size=1> I think any cleric would tell you that all their mana is better than being dead. <br>
